    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Sharpening filter is achieved by</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>α</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>∗</mo><mi>H</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F + \\alpha ( F - F * H )</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span> is the image and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">H</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span></span> is the Gaussian kernel. A blured image is\nattained by convolving <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">H</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>I.e. Sharpening filter is achieved by blurring the image then subtracting\nthe \"blur\" out of the original image.</p>\n<p>The assignment is posted\non <a href=\"https://github.com/arshiannafi/uvic/tree/main/ece-471-computer-vision/sharpening-filter\">GitHub</a>\n.</p>","frontmatter":{"headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":0.752,"src":"/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/0f0a2/pear-before-after.png","srcSet":"/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/bef91/pear-before-after.png 94w,\n/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/e0c5e/pear-before-after.png 188w,\n/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/0f0a2/pear-before-after.png 375w,\n/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/d115f/pear-before-after.png 563w,\n/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/ec2b8/pear-before-after.png 750w,\n/static/814a05ec2356c5d725a156f2e2853b61/055b7/pear-before-after.png 780w","sizes":"(max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px"}}},"headerImageAlt":"Image of a pear before and after applying the sharpening filter","headerImageCopyright":"","slug":"/pages/uvic/ece-471/sharpening-filter","pageTitle":"ECE 471 - Sharpening Filter","pageDescription":"This page discusses how sharpening filters works and links to the assignment. The assignment is for UVic ECE 471 Computer Vision and uses OpenCV and Python.","author":"A. Annafi","last_modified":"2022-05-23","tags":["ece-471","computer-vision","sharpening-filter","Python","OpenCV"]}}},"pageContext":{"id":"e59be8ec-f104-5113-8d99-28cca44d7021","frontmatter__slug":"/pages/uvic/ece-471/sharpening-filter","__params":{"frontmatter__slug":"pages"}}},
